Hillary Mageka @hillarymageka A parliamentary caucus against corruption wants National Treasury Cabinet secretary Henry Rotich and Kerio Valley Development Authority CEO David Kimosop to vacate office pending investigations into the construction of Arror and Kimwarer dams in Elgeyo Marakwet county. At the same time, African Parliamentarians Network Against Corruption-Kenya (APNAC-K) wants all Cabinet Secretaries and Principal Secretaries mentioned in corruption scandals to step aside to allow for  investigations. “The caucus believes that it is in the best interest of the CS’s adversely mentioned in the scandal to step aside to allow a thorough probe to be done,” the caucus said in a press statement signed by the chair MP Shakeel Shabbir (Kisumu East).